HEADWORD: Diagnostics
<hw>Di`ag*nos"tics</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That part of
medicine which has to do with ascertaining the nature of diseases by
means of their symptoms or signs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His rare skill in <qex>diagnostics</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Diagometer</ent>⟦br⟧
